Below is a short guide on creating Aliases and Desktop Shortcuts in Windows - To Shutdown, Lock, and pull up PowerShell.

First ensure you have a $PROFILE file via PowerShell setup to run variables when you first launch  your computer:

New-Item -Type File -Force $PROFILE

Then open the file in notepad with:
notepad $PROFILE

Enter any desired aliases, here we will be creating one to shutdown your computer.

New-Alias -Name shutdown -Value Stop-Computer
